gonna have time

21:26.328 --> 21:27.329
to read them
one of these days.

21:27.416 --> 21:29.549
Well, if you get the chance,

21:30.245 --> 21:33.204
I recommend anything
by Dennis Lehane.

21:33.814 --> 21:36.599
-You take honey?
-Yes, please.

21:36.730 --> 21:38.558
Herodotus: The Histories.

21:38.688 --> 21:41.082
Wooh...
Found that one challenging,

21:41.212 --> 21:42.388
but worth it.

21:42.475 --> 21:44.215
Wow. Where do you
find the time?

21:44.564 --> 21:46.000
Uh, well, I had a lotta time in...

21:46.130 --> 21:49.308
Uh, in... somnia.

21:50.570 --> 21:52.746
You know, in fact, if you have
anything that's really boring

21:52.876 --> 21:53.964
you wouldn't mind
loaning me,

21:54.095 --> 21:56.097
I'm trying to render
myself unconscious.

21:56.227 --> 21:57.707
I've got just the thing.

21:58.186 --> 22:00.406
You just have
to promise

22:00.536 --> 22:02.495
to return it to
the library on time.

22:06.542 --> 22:08.718
-Lakeside City Journal.
-Uh-huh.

22:08.849 --> 22:11.591
[scoffing]
"2000 to 2004."

22:12.069 --> 22:14.028
I was researching a story.

22:14.681 --> 22:17.901
I've also got 2005 to 2018.

22:18.032 --> 22:20.426
-I am already sleepy.
-Right?

22:20.556 --> 22:21.949
I'm the editor
of the goddamn newspaper

22:22.079 --> 22:23.037
and I couldn't
keep my eyes open.

22:24.734 --> 22:26.649
♪

22:27.389 --> 22:28.956
I think Alison's gonna turn up.

22:31.567 --> 22:33.874
-I hope you're right.
-I'm sure of it.

22:34.004 --> 22:35.658
[door opening]

22:36.267 --> 22:37.791
-[door closing]
-Hey, Mom.

22:37.878 --> 22:38.966
Oh, hey.

22:39.358 --> 22:40.576
Leon, this is--

22:40.707 --> 22:42.099
I thought you said
you didn't like him.

22:45.451 --> 22:47.931
We just got off
on the wrong foot.

22:49.455 --> 22:51.761
Mike, this is
my youngest, Leon.

22:51.892 --> 22:53.372
Leon, this is Mike.

22:53.502 --> 22:55.417
-Hi.
-Hey.

22:55.809 --> 22:57.376
Why don't you get started
on your homework?

22:57.463 --> 22:58.725
Dinner'll be ready
in a half-hour.

23:03.469 --> 23:05.601
I guess I should go.

23:05.732 --> 23:08.256
Um, I'll let you guys
have dinner.

23:10.084 --> 23:11.172
Thanks for the tea.

23:13.914 --> 23:16.743
Thanks for
the added security...

23:16.873 --> 23:18.571
Attempt at added security.

23:18.701 --> 23:20.573
-You're welcome.
-Oh, and...

23:21.574 --> 23:23.619
As long as you're going
to the library...

23:24.490 --> 23:26.753
Uh-huh. Well, okay.

23:27.493 --> 23:29.146
Sure they're not
gonna put me in a coma?

23:29.277 --> 23:31.497
No guarantees.
I'll get the door.

23:34.369 --> 23:35.762
[sighing]

23:35.936 --> 23:38.242
♪

23:56.522 --> 23:58.219
[whispering voices]

23:58.349 --> 23:59.786
[moaning]

23:59.873 --> 24:01.309
[wind blowing]

24:05.792 --> 24:07.315
[phone vibrating]

24:09.360 --> 24:10.797
[phone vibrating]

24:16.629 --> 24:18.152
[phone vibrating]

24:34.603 --> 24:37.519
♪

24:54.014 --> 24:55.798
[knocking on door]

24:58.366 --> 25:00.411
[door handle rattling]

25:03.371 --> 25:05.460
[electric saw buzzing]

25:11.118 --> 25:13.033
[electric saw buzzing]

25:17.211 --> 25:18.168
[banging]

25:19.256 --> 25:20.954
[Hank] Look, Mr. Wednesday, I--

25:21.084 --> 25:22.869
[Mr. Wednesday] Just Wednesday to you, Hank.

25:23.913 --> 25:25.959
I'd love to accommodate
your request, really I would,

25:26.046 --> 25:28.222
but I can't just release
Miss Wells into your custody.

25:28.309 --> 25:30.267
-That's not how it works.
-Not even for true love?

25:30.398 --> 25:32.748
[sighing]
No, unfortunately not.

25:32.879 --> 25:36.012
She's under the care of
a court-appointed conservator.

25:36.709 --> 25:38.928
Here.
Larry Hutchinson.

25:39.059 --> 25:40.626
-He's the one
you need to talk to.
-Hmm...

25:40.756 --> 25:42.497
And, with all due
respect, sir,

25:42.628 --> 25:44.760
Miss Wells didn't seem
all that glad to see you.

25:44.891 --> 25:46.545
Oh, I shouldn't have
taken her by surprise.

25:46.675 --> 25:49.199
I should've remembered
she always hated surprises.

25:50.810 --> 25:52.812
♪

26:33.853 --> 26:36.029
[crackling]

26:38.553 --> 26:42.470
[neons buzzing]

26:43.645 --> 26:46.648
[Rosa Parks]
The light is out.
I have lost.

26:47.344 --> 26:49.825
[Harriet Tubman]
They have stripped me
of my dignity.

26:49.956 --> 26:53.655
I have the right
to liberty or dignity.

26:54.525 --> 26:57.572
[Nina Simone]
Their greed will
swallow me whole.

26:57.703 --> 27:00.357
[Bilquis]
Come find me, Shadow Moon.

27:00.531 --> 27:03.447
♪

27:03.578 --> 27:07.713
[neons buzzing]

27:11.064 --> 27:13.675
[ice crackling]

27:22.118 --> 27:25.121
♪

27:40.267 --> 27:41.834
[wind roaring]

27:43.357 --> 27:44.314
[moaning]

28:03.551 --> 28:05.161
♪

28:06.206 --> 28:08.208
[breathing deeply]

28:11.777 --> 28:13.953
[creaking]

28:16.433 --> 28:17.608
Who the fuck are you?

28:18.305 --> 28:19.654
Is she supposed
to be here already?

28:19.785 --> 28:20.873
Not as far as I know.

28:21.003 --> 28:22.439
'Cause no one told me.

28:22.570 --> 28:23.876
And I'm supposed to go on break.

28:24.006 --> 28:25.704
Anybody wanna tell me
what the deal is here?

28:25.791 --> 28:26.922
[woman]
Maybe I should call upstairs.

28:27.053 --> 28:28.445
-Hello?
-Why?

28:29.011 --> 28:31.492
To find out that nobody knows
anything about anything

28:31.622 --> 28:33.407
except it's
someone else's fault?

28:33.494 --> 28:34.800
You already know that.

28:34.887 --> 28:36.323
That's why they
call it Purgatory.

28:36.453 --> 28:38.238
Um, hey, I'm talking to you.

28:38.325 --> 28:40.631
Working in Hell
would be a promotion.

28:40.762 --> 28:42.155
Are you fucking people deaf?

28:43.591 --> 28:45.332
-Hi.
-Who are you?

28:45.462 --> 28:46.899
AV Guy.

28:47.377 --> 28:49.510
1940's usherette.

28:50.424 --> 28:52.121
[woman] The 1940's thing has nothing to do with you.

28:52.252 --> 28:54.733
This is just...
what they gave me.

28:55.298 --> 28:56.822
We're your facilitators.

28:57.387 --> 28:59.694
Okay. Well, how about

28:59.825 --> 29:01.914
you facilitate me
the fuck outta here?

29:02.044 --> 29:04.743
Well, first you need to
acknowledge reality.

29:04.873 --> 29:06.570
Like it says in your pamphlet.

29:06.701 --> 29:09.182
Yeah. I... I already
threw that thing

29:09.312 --> 29:11.140
in the face of another
stupid fucking idiot.

29:11.271 --> 29:13.316
Will ya listen to
the potty mouth on this one.

29:18.408 --> 29:20.497
Oh, creeping Mother of Christ,

29:20.628 --> 29:23.283
please tell me we are not doing
The Life of Laura Moon.

29:23.413 --> 29:24.414
You might learn something.

29:27.591 --> 29:29.985
Do the words "rest in peace"
mean nothing to you people?

29:30.116 --> 29:31.160
It was my fucking life.

29:31.291 --> 29:33.032
I lived it with
my eyes wide open.

29:33.119 --> 29:34.903
There's nothing
to rehash. Period.

29:35.034 --> 29:35.991
Over and out.

29:39.516 --> 29:40.779
And, by the way, who here

29:40.866 --> 29:43.259
is such a fucking
expert on my life

29:43.390 --> 29:45.740
that this little shit show's
even gonna make any sense?

29:45.827 --> 29:47.133
[tapping]

29:48.221 --> 29:49.744
-[man] Here you go.
-[girl] I'm tired.

29:49.875 --> 29:50.963
That would be you.

29:51.050 --> 29:52.442
[man] Kiddo.

29:52.529 --> 29:54.096
[woman] Welcome to the Midwesterner Motel.

29:54.227 --> 29:57.404
Okay. Just give me one more second.

29:57.534 --> 29:58.405
That's my dad.

29:59.232 --> 30:00.320
Oh, he's so young.

30:02.496 --> 30:05.020
My apologies, there's only one
non-smoking room left.

30:05.151 --> 30:08.458
A double queen, which is...

30:08.589 --> 30:10.243
50 more a night.

30:10.373 --> 30:12.811
Gee, that's a little steep.

30:13.724 --> 30:15.552
Considering my daughter's allergies,

30:15.639 --> 30:18.207
I... figured it didn't hurt to ask, right?

30:18.338 --> 30:19.687
Oh, she's so adorable.

30:19.774 --> 30:22.124
[snoring]

30:22.255 --> 30:23.430
I'll just slip you
in that room.

30:24.257 --> 30:25.084
Don't you worry.

30:27.521 --> 30:29.088
[Laura]
Yeah, I know.

30:29.610 --> 30:31.177
I was there for fucksake.

30:31.264 --> 30:32.787
Shh! It's better
if you just watch.

30:32.918 --> 30:33.788
[sighing]

30:37.226 --> 30:38.401
[sighing]

30:38.532 --> 30:39.838
[Laura] Let me tell you how this went.

30:40.926 --> 30:42.928
While my dad was chatting up
the hotel clerk,

30:43.058 --> 30:44.668
I was working
a different angle.

30:45.365 --> 30:47.019
I was really pissed at my mom
for not coming with us.

30:47.149 --> 30:48.803
[phone ringing]

30:48.934 --> 30:50.674
Are you here for
the state fair, as well?

30:50.805 --> 30:53.025
I wish.
Visiting family.

30:53.155 --> 30:54.287
[clerk]
Here are the keys
to your room.

30:55.375 --> 30:56.637
Enjoy your stay.

30:56.724 --> 30:57.943
Okay, kiddo.

30:58.073 --> 31:01.381
Looks like we got
two queen-size beds.

31:02.034 --> 31:04.558
So, to get back at my mom,
I said to my dad,

31:04.688 --> 31:06.473
"Maybe you should help
the pretty lady with her bags."

31:09.955 --> 31:11.130
Excuse me, Miss.

31:11.217 --> 31:12.653
Which of course he did,
in a heartbeat

31:12.783 --> 31:15.743
because she's hot
and he's... "helpful".

31:17.353 --> 31:18.746
♪

31:20.661 --> 31:22.402
Turns out we were all staying
on the same floor.

31:22.532 --> 31:25.187
So, being a kid, I asked,
since they have a pool,

31:25.274 --> 31:26.623
"Dad, can we go swimming?"

31:26.710 --> 31:27.886
I don't see why not.

31:28.016 --> 31:29.365
You wanna come?

31:29.496 --> 31:31.541
I don't wanna intrude
on family time.

31:31.672 --> 31:32.891
Oh, you're not intruding.

31:33.456 --> 31:34.370
Is she, Dad?

31:35.371 --> 31:36.329
Not one bit.

31:39.462 --> 31:41.073
But once it was time
to go swimming,

31:41.203 --> 31:43.118
I told Dad I'd changed my mind.

31:43.249 --> 31:45.468
I just wanted to stay
in the room and watch cartoons.

31:47.296 --> 31:48.515
[sighing]

31:48.645 --> 31:49.995
But I told him that
he should go without me.

31:53.346 --> 31:55.522
♪

31:57.872 --> 31:59.482
-Hi.
-Hi.

32:00.005 --> 32:01.180
Where's your daughter?

32:01.789 --> 32:04.096
Oh, she decided
to stay in the room

32:04.226 --> 32:05.445
and watch cartoons.

32:05.532 --> 32:06.576
[woman laughing]

32:06.707 --> 32:07.708
I can't believe

32:07.838 --> 32:09.405
you told them
it was closed.

32:09.536 --> 32:12.017
Oh, well, we got
the pool to ourselves,
though, didn't we?

32:12.452 --> 32:15.063
-Yes.
-So, then it worked.

32:15.542 --> 32:17.500
Well, good night.

32:19.807 --> 32:20.721
Good night.

32:29.338 --> 32:32.254
♪

32:34.648 --> 32:36.693
After their swim,
the fun continued.

32:37.390 --> 32:38.869
-Dad called "Marco".
-[door closing]

32:39.000 --> 32:40.654
She said "Polo",
and that was that.

32:43.613 --> 32:44.701
Dad was so into this chick,

32:44.832 --> 32:46.007
he didn't even
notice me snooping.

32:47.139 --> 32:48.096
[door opening]

32:52.535 --> 32:54.320
♪

32:54.450 --> 32:55.712
[woman]
I've gotta get out
of these wet clothes.

32:55.799 --> 32:56.583
Don't go anywhere.

32:56.757 --> 32:58.411
♪

32:58.541 --> 32:59.412
[Laura's father]
Okay, you go ahead
and do that.

32:59.499 --> 33:00.152
I'm gonna
make you a drink.

33:00.282 --> 33:01.414
What do you want?

33:01.544 --> 33:03.372
Weird choice of music,
but whatever.

33:03.503 --> 33:04.591
[woman]
I'll have whatever
you're having.

33:04.721 --> 33:05.809
[Laura's father]
What's that? I can't...

33:05.896 --> 33:06.854
You know what?
I can't hear ya.

33:06.941 --> 33:08.073
I'm just gonna
make something.

33:08.203 --> 33:09.596
I'm gonna make you
a surprise.

33:09.726 --> 33:11.598
[woman]
You are so cute!

33:20.520 --> 33:22.000
And then, it was all
downhill from there.

33:23.610 --> 33:25.177
It really is better
if you just watch.

33:26.134 --> 33:28.354
I think maybe we could just
fast-forward through the rest.

33:28.484 --> 33:32.227
And then you can give me my
get-out-of-Purgatory-free card
and we can part friends.

33:32.575 --> 33:34.142
We don't actually make deals.

33:38.494 --> 33:40.583
Beautiful work, Cordelia.

33:41.715 --> 33:44.587
A remarkable facsimile
of the original document.

33:44.979 --> 33:47.155
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

33:47.547 --> 33:49.288
[Cordelia]
You said 1779,

33:49.418 --> 33:51.420
but I figured you meant 1979.

33:51.551 --> 33:53.857
Just feels like
250 years sometimes.

33:53.988 --> 33:55.511
[laughing]

33:55.642 --> 33:56.773
Is she really your wife?

33:58.123 --> 34:00.168
-Would I lie to you?
-Honestly?

34:00.473 --> 34:01.604
I don't know.

34:02.475 --> 34:04.999
Demeter is most
certainly my wife

34:05.130 --> 34:07.393
and also one of the most
remarkable creatures

34:07.523 --> 34:09.308
to ever grace this planet.

34:09.438 --> 34:12.006
Hmm, her beauty only
matched by her keen wit,

34:12.137 --> 34:14.530
droll sense of humor,
and generosity of spirit.

34:14.617 --> 34:15.923
Wow.

34:16.576 --> 34:18.534
Where did you ever
meet this...

34:18.969 --> 34:20.319
-...goddess?
-Goddess is right.

34:21.885 --> 34:26.455
On a small,
unprepossessing farm

34:26.586 --> 34:28.109
-in rural--
-[phone ringing]

34:29.154 --> 34:30.111
Sorry.

34:31.373 --> 34:32.896
-[sighing]
-It's Wisconsin.

34:32.983 --> 34:34.289
Probably your son.

34:34.420 --> 34:36.813
Oh, and I wonder
how Shadow got the number.

34:36.944 --> 34:38.119
I gave it to him
at the memorial.

34:38.206 --> 34:39.599
Chummy, aren't we?

34:40.687 --> 34:42.950
I just thought he might need
to get in touch with you.

34:43.255 --> 34:44.299
Should I send it to voicemail?

34:44.430 --> 34:46.388
No, the moment has been lost.

34:47.607 --> 34:48.564
Carry on.

34:49.348 --> 34:50.349
Hello?

34:50.479 --> 34:52.002
[cawing]

34:52.133 --> 34:52.960
[Cordelia]
Yeah, I'm good.

34:55.005 --> 34:56.398
He wants to talk to you.

34:56.572 --> 34:58.879
♪

35:03.797 --> 35:05.277
-Hi.
-Hey.

35:05.407 --> 35:06.495
I need to see Bilquis.

35:06.582 --> 35:07.757
Any idea where
I can find her?

35:07.844 --> 35:09.846
Oh, I'm fine. Thank you
for asking, son.

35:09.977 --> 35:11.196
And how are you?

35:11.457 --> 35:13.154
I just saw you a few days ago.

35:13.285 --> 35:15.069
A lot can happen
in a few days.

35:15.156 --> 35:17.506
Bilquis, do you know
where she is?

35:18.159 --> 35:19.465
I do. And would you find out
what happened

35:19.595 --> 35:21.293
with Technical Boy
if you see her?

35:21.423 --> 35:22.468
Technical Boy?

35:23.860 --> 35:24.861
You know this how?

35:24.992 --> 35:27.647
[cawing]

35:27.777 --> 35:29.475
You know what?
It doesn't even matter.

35:29.605 --> 35:30.693
I just need to speak to her.

35:30.824 --> 35:32.130
It's about your
dreams, isn't it?

35:35.742 --> 35:37.874
Her address, please.

35:40.225 --> 35:41.139
New York City.

35:41.269 --> 35:42.923
1860 East 20th Street,

35:43.053 --> 35:44.446
Apartment 12C.

35:44.533 --> 35:45.447
And if--

35:46.187 --> 35:47.319
[beeping]

35:48.624 --> 35:50.626
♪

35:50.757 --> 35:52.106
[grunts]

35:52.237 --> 35:53.890
"How sharper than
the serpent's tooth it is

35:54.021 --> 35:55.631
to have a thankless child."

35:57.720 --> 35:58.852
Forty years.

36:00.506 --> 36:01.420
Impressive.

36:01.550 --> 36:02.812
Hmm.

36:03.900 --> 36:06.338
Odd that Miss Wells never
mentioned she was married.

36:07.382 --> 36:09.776
We thought we had the key
to an enduring union...

36:10.777 --> 36:13.997
cherishing the spaces
in our relationship.

36:14.824 --> 36:18.654
Sadly, a few screws went loose
during our last sabbatical.

36:18.785 --> 36:20.395
-Indeed.
-Mm.

36:20.526 --> 36:22.049
Trying to convince the judge

36:22.180 --> 36:24.312
that prancing around
in public stark naked...

36:24.399 --> 36:27.663
comports with her status
as a "goddess"

36:28.186 --> 36:29.665
is pretty out there.

36:29.796 --> 36:33.800
Well, nudity is not lewdity,
as they say.

36:33.930 --> 36:34.975
Well...

36:36.759 --> 36:38.370
As you know,
Judge Trakes appointed me

36:38.500 --> 36:40.023
Miss Wells' conservator

36:40.154 --> 36:42.200
in the absence of
any family members.

36:42.330 --> 36:44.114
Oh, she's obviously been
well cared for.

36:44.245 --> 36:46.029
For that, I will be
forever grateful.

36:46.160 --> 36:47.814
I just hope she's not been

36:47.901 --> 36:50.817
a burden on the state,
financially.

36:50.947 --> 36:52.340
Heavens, no.

36:53.036 --> 36:55.213
Your wife's capacity
may be diminished,

36:55.343 --> 36:57.345
but her portfolio
is robust.

36:57.693 --> 36:58.738
Oh, that's my girl.

36:59.304 --> 37:00.218
[door closing]

37:04.613 --> 37:06.006
Hey, I was looking for you.

37:06.136 --> 37:07.529
I just left a note
with Leon.

37:08.574 --> 37:10.445
Oh, you going somewhere?

37:10.576 --> 37:11.881
Yeah. I gotta go
to New York

37:12.012 --> 37:12.882
to see a friend.

37:15.145 --> 37:17.452
-Still no word, huh?
-No.

37:18.410 --> 37:20.586
They have a couple more search
parties out today, but, uh...

37:21.935 --> 37:23.415
Nothing so far.

37:24.416 --> 37:26.766
-You okay?
-Yeah, you know, it's just...

37:26.896 --> 37:28.376
The longer she's gone...

37:33.686 --> 37:34.600
Stay safe.

37:38.168 --> 37:39.300
[door opening]

37:40.693 --> 37:41.563
[door closing]

37:51.181 --> 37:53.880
♪

38:04.673 --> 38:05.500
[scoffing]

38:11.506 --> 38:13.334
♪

38:15.815 --> 38:16.685
[door opening]

38:23.605 --> 38:24.650
Fuck have you been?

38:24.780 --> 38:26.086
Batteries were dead.

38:26.173 --> 38:28.436
Took a while finding
some new ones.

38:28.567 --> 38:31.091
Things have a way of
getting lost around here.

38:31.178 --> 38:33.180
Well, scary movie's
almost over.

38:33.311 --> 38:35.182
And then with any luck,
you guys'll be lost as well.

38:35.965 --> 38:37.402
Okay, so...

38:37.576 --> 38:39.012
♪

38:39.142 --> 38:40.666
Dad fucked everything in sight
except for Mom.

38:40.796 --> 38:42.755
Mom paid him back in kind,
tit for tat.

38:42.842 --> 38:44.713
And if there is
a God in heaven,

38:44.800 --> 38:46.411
I will not have to
sit here and watch that.

38:47.107 --> 38:49.762
I followed in
my father's fucksteps

38:49.892 --> 38:51.720
with every broken boy
I could find.

38:51.851 --> 38:53.331
If they weren't broken already,

38:53.461 --> 38:54.549
then they were once I was
finished with them.

38:56.943 --> 38:57.987
♪

39:01.077 --> 39:02.122
I got married.

39:04.429 --> 39:05.343
Um...

39:07.606 --> 39:09.347
Royally fucked that up.
Died.

39:09.477 --> 39:10.826
And here we are!

39:11.871 --> 39:13.263
So...
[clearing throat]

39:13.742 --> 39:15.004
What have we
learned here today?

39:16.484 --> 39:17.877
Not a fucking thing.

39:18.878 --> 39:21.010
I could've told you before
I ever got to this shithole

39:21.141 --> 39:23.056
that I am the architect
of every fucked-up thing

39:23.186 --> 39:24.362
that ever happened in my life.

39:25.841 --> 39:27.626
That's on me.
I'm aware of that.

39:27.756 --> 39:29.454
I'm... I'm okay with that.

39:30.324 --> 39:32.195
I aided and abetted
my dad's sport fucking,

39:32.282 --> 39:33.893
which led to my mom's
revenge fucking.

39:34.023 --> 39:35.547
His drinking, her drinking.

39:35.634 --> 39:37.592
I became my dad,
did my own fucking fucking,

39:37.723 --> 39:39.986
fucked up my marriage
and my life.

39:40.334 --> 39:41.335
The end.

39:44.294 --> 39:45.861
Tell me something
I don't fucking know.

39:46.775 --> 39:48.124
You've really wasted
your time here.

39:48.821 --> 39:51.519
And Grandpa's time,
and mine.

39:51.998 --> 39:54.392
On bullshit that is not only obvious,

39:54.522 --> 39:56.132
but redundantly obvious.

39:58.396 --> 40:00.441
This whole place
is kinda just

40:00.572 --> 40:02.051
a bunch of fucking
hallways to nowhere.

40:04.445 --> 40:06.316
If you already know all the answers,

40:07.187 --> 40:09.058
what is it that you're
still so angry about?

40:10.930 --> 40:12.322
Sanctimonious fuckheads
like you.

40:17.110 --> 40:18.024
[splashing]

40:20.113 --> 40:22.550
♪

40:44.485 --> 40:45.747
[gasping]

40:45.878 --> 40:47.488
[panting]

40:50.273 --> 40:51.361
What's wrong with me?

40:51.492 --> 40:53.755
[panting]

40:57.542 --> 41:01.328
When I saw this,
all I could think of was you,

41:01.807 --> 41:03.722
standing in that field,

41:04.200 --> 41:06.681
with the sun setting behind you

41:06.812 --> 41:09.728
on that farm in Pennsylvania.

41:09.858 --> 41:12.295
I don't need new clothes,
Ofnir.

41:12.382 --> 41:14.080
It's for our court appearance,
my love.

41:14.559 --> 41:17.562
I don't need flowers
or chocolates.

41:18.301 --> 41:20.216
Well, we have to explain
that your husband's back

41:20.347 --> 41:21.740
and able to take care of you,

41:21.870 --> 41:26.440
so the judge can transfer
the conservatorship back to me

41:26.571 --> 41:28.050
and we can get you
the hell out of here.

41:28.181 --> 41:29.487
You're not listening to me.

41:29.617 --> 41:30.749
As for that guy, Hutchinson,

41:30.879 --> 41:32.490
huh, what a charlatan
he is, huh?

41:32.577 --> 41:33.708
[chuckling]

41:33.839 --> 41:35.014
You know, he actually
admitted to me--

41:35.144 --> 41:36.276
Well, you never did.

41:36.363 --> 41:37.930
...that he is the conservator

41:38.017 --> 41:40.454
for at least half-a-dozen
"residents" in here.

41:40.585 --> 41:43.152
And I found out that he owns
half this place.

41:43.283 --> 41:45.764
You know, I'd give him
high marks for conmanship

41:45.894 --> 41:47.505
if it wasn't
such a personal matter.

41:47.592 --> 41:48.593
I don't wanna leave.

41:50.464 --> 41:52.510
-No, you can't mean that.
-Oh, I mean it.

41:52.640 --> 41:54.947
I am my true self here.

41:56.296 --> 41:59.386
People accept me
as a goddess.

41:59.473 --> 42:01.693
They actually worship me.

42:01.780 --> 42:02.868
[chuckling]

42:02.998 --> 42:05.131
I had forgotten
how good that feels.

42:07.960 --> 42:10.353
You tell the loons in here
you're the Lizard King,

42:10.484 --> 42:11.703
they'd worship you.

42:11.964 --> 42:15.358
We are gods, you and I.

42:15.489 --> 42:18.623
And this is a mental
institution, not a temple.

42:18.753 --> 42:21.713
And what's going on in here
is sacrilege.

42:22.104 --> 42:23.192
And the sooner
we get you outta here

42:23.279 --> 42:24.280
and off your meds,
you'll realize that.

42:24.454 --> 42:25.934
♪

42:26.065 --> 42:27.893
Now, why are you here, Ofnir?

42:30.069 --> 42:31.549
-Well, for you.
-For me?

42:31.636 --> 42:32.767
-Mm.
-Ah.

42:32.854 --> 42:35.161
-Not for my money?
-Oh.

42:35.509 --> 42:36.771
Well, I know,
I know that you're

42:36.902 --> 42:39.295
beating the drum
for some war.

42:40.166 --> 42:42.385
Hmm... And wars
are expensive.

42:42.472 --> 42:45.127
Just... just
be honest with me.

42:48.261 --> 42:51.003
If you're honest with me,
I'll go with you.

42:52.831 --> 42:55.485
-Trick question.
-It's asked of a trickster.

43:00.012 --> 43:03.406
I say I'm here guided
by my undying love for you,

43:03.537 --> 43:05.191
you'll call me a liar and say

43:05.321 --> 43:08.629
where the hell have you been
for the last 250 years?

43:08.760 --> 43:11.371
Hmm, that you're incapable
of loving anyone but yourself.

43:11.458 --> 43:13.852
If I say I'm here
for your money,

43:13.982 --> 43:16.594
then you'll call me a
craven, acquisitive heel.

43:16.724 --> 43:18.160
No, no, we both know
each other too well

43:18.291 --> 43:20.685
for me to fall
for that bait. Nah.

43:21.947 --> 43:25.907
There was a time
when I knew you
or thought I did.

43:26.038 --> 43:29.476
But... And now,
when I look at you,

43:29.607 --> 43:34.046
I see a god who has grown
old and... and desperate.

43:35.525 --> 43:36.657
The question is,

43:38.180 --> 43:39.791
what are you desperate for?

43:43.403 --> 43:46.232
♪

43:46.798 --> 43:48.016
[footsteps approaching]

43:50.062 --> 43:51.237
[videotape whirring]

43:52.238 --> 43:53.413
Ah. Say nothing.

43:54.501 --> 43:55.937
Do nothing.

43:57.373 --> 43:59.027
Just watch.

44:01.377 --> 44:03.815
♪

44:03.945 --> 44:06.078
[Laura's father]
Excuse me, Miss.
That looks heavy.

44:06.644 --> 44:08.210
Mind if I give you
a hand with that?

44:08.515 --> 44:09.342
[woman]
Thank you.

44:10.299 --> 44:11.170
A real gentleman.

44:13.259 --> 44:14.695
Does this pretty little girl

44:14.826 --> 44:17.089
know that her daddy
is an endangered species?

44:20.309 --> 44:21.659
Okay. Come on, sweetie.

44:22.224 --> 44:23.661
[woman]
You're so sweet
to carry that.

44:23.791 --> 44:25.445
I'm here for
my sister's birthday,

44:25.575 --> 44:28.013
but they have a tiny place,
so I decided to stay here.

44:29.014 --> 44:30.450
Well, this is me.

44:31.059 --> 44:32.104
We're right down there.

44:33.888 --> 44:35.411
That pool downstairs sure looks inviting.

44:35.542 --> 44:37.065
Would you ladies like to go for a swim?

44:37.196 --> 44:39.198
I could be persuaded.

44:39.285 --> 44:41.287
That is,
if I wouldn't be intruding.

44:41.896 --> 44:42.680
[Laura's father]
Not at all.

44:43.724 --> 44:45.160
I'll just get changed.

44:45.726 --> 44:46.945
Come get me
when you're ready.

44:47.510 --> 44:48.598
Okay.
Come on, sweetie.

44:50.775 --> 44:53.691
So, I didn't see
a kid's pool down there.

44:53.821 --> 44:56.955
So it's okay if you want
to stay in the hotel room
and watch cartoons.

44:57.825 --> 45:00.698
There might even be
some candy in the mini-bar.

45:01.524 --> 45:02.438
How's that sound?

45:03.352 --> 45:05.006
-Okay.
-Okay.

45:11.621 --> 45:12.840
[woman]
I've gotta get out
of these wet clothes.

45:13.406 --> 45:15.016
Don't go anywhere.

45:15.103 --> 45:16.539
[Laura's father] Okay, you go ahead and do that.

45:16.670 --> 45:18.454
I'm gonna make you a drink.
What do you want?

45:18.585 --> 45:20.456
[woman laughing]

45:20.587 --> 45:22.241
[woman]
I'll... I'll have
whatever you're having.

45:22.371 --> 45:23.590
[Laura's father]
What's that? You know what?

45:23.721 --> 45:24.939
I can't hear ya.
I'm just gonna make something.

45:25.070 --> 45:26.593
I'm gonna make you
a surprise.

45:26.898 --> 45:28.508
[woman]
You are so cute!

45:36.951 --> 45:39.258
♪

45:39.388 --> 45:40.433
I was just a little kid.

45:42.217 --> 45:43.349
I was just a little kid.

45:45.612 --> 45:48.702
Who wasn't the architect
of every fucked-up thing
in your life.

45:49.311 --> 45:51.183
Or the one who ruined
your parents' marriage.

45:51.792 --> 45:52.750
[crying]

45:59.452 --> 46:00.888
There wasn't anything wrong
with me.

46:01.019 --> 46:01.976
[sighing]

46:03.499 --> 46:04.631
They should've
protected you.

46:11.072 --> 46:13.553
I mean, it would've been great
if I'd have known that

46:13.683 --> 46:15.729
before I started
fucking up my own life.

46:15.860 --> 46:16.730
[sniffing]

46:18.166 --> 46:20.647
Or, you know,
while I was still alive.

46:21.430 --> 46:22.954
Well, now you know.

46:24.477 --> 46:25.391
Yeah.

46:29.743 --> 46:31.745
Great.
Are we done here?

46:31.832 --> 46:32.746
Cool.

46:35.880 --> 46:36.794
Okay.

46:38.404 --> 46:39.666
[indistinct chatter]

46:39.840 --> 46:41.494
♪

